It is a historic event as it is seven years since the central bank cut interest rates to zero.
For the first time, we are getting closer to a situation where a key central bank has a chance to get out of the zero level and start normalizing interest rates," said Angel Ubide, senior fellow at the Peterson Institue for International Economics.
