Eight golden rules for living in a student dormitory
It's been 11 years since, as an ignorant 19-year-old, I moved into a student dormitory. Back then, I still believed in berets and moral relativism, but only now can I remember the forced smiles of the people I irritated - and the numerous, long complaints about others.
